</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Specification_allocation +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation">
<p>
 A <b>Specification_allocation</b> is the association between an 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> and one or more of an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>, an 
<express_ref linkend="Configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Product_configuration"/>, an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>, an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_element"/>, 
one or more of an <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum"/>, 
one or more of an 
<express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Inter_stratum_feature"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Laminate_component"/>, or a 
<express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum_feature"/> 
that results from the design activity.
When the <b>identifier_in_target_context</b> is supplied, only one <b>target_product_object</b> shall be supplied, to support the uniqueness requirement.
</p></ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation.the_context"><p>
the first <b>target_product_object</b></p>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation.identifier_in_target_context"><p>
specifies the string that is unique within the context of the <b>target_product_object</b>
for the <b>Specification_allocation</b>.  The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</p><note>
The <b>identifier_in_target_context</b> may be mapped to the value for an item find number in enterprise systems that include specifications in list of materials.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation.purpose"><p>
the text that specifies the <b>purpose</b> for the <b>Specification_allocation</b>.
</p><example>
An enterprise may define a <b>purpose</b> to be 'item find number'.
</example>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation.target_product_object">
specifies either an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>, an 
<express_ref linkend="Configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Product_configuration"/>, an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>, an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_usage_view:arm:Physical_unit_usage_view_arm.Part_feature"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition"/> a 
<express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_element"/>, 
or one of 
an <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/>, a 
<express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_item_identification"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/>, a <express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_item_identification"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum"/> or one of an <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Inter_stratum_feature"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Laminate_component"/>,
a <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum_feature"/>, or a 
<express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum_surface"/> 
as the target through which the 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> is 
realized by the <b>Specification_allocation</b>.  There shall be one or more  
<express_ref linkend="Product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>,  
<express_ref linkend="Configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Product_configuration"/>,  
<express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>, 
 <express_ref linkend="Product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>,  
 <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_usage_view:arm:Physical_unit_usage_view_arm.Part_feature"/>,  
 <express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_definition"/>,  
 <express_ref linkend="Physical_connectivity_definition:arm:Physical_connectivity_definition_arm.Physical_connectivity_element"/>, 
 <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Assembly_component"/>,  
 <express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_item_identification"/>,  <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:arm:Component_feature_arm.Component_feature"/>,  <express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_item_identification"/>,  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum"/>, 
 <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Inter_stratum_feature"/>,  
 <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Laminate_component"/>,  
 <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum_feature"/>, or  
 <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:arm:Layered_interconnect_module_design_arm.Stratum_surface"/> 
 for a <b>Specification_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation.allocated_specification">
specifies the role of the 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/>
for the <b>Specification_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation.wr:WR1">
If the <b>identifier_in_target_context</b> exists, then the size of <b>target_product_object</b> shall be one.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_allocation.ur:UR1">
The combination of <b>identifier_in_target_context</b> and the first element of <b>target_product_object</b> shall be unique 
within a population of <b>Specification_allocation</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Specification_definition +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition">

An <b>Specification_definition</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>. An 
<b>Specification_definition</b> may be either a 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Design_specification"/>, 
a <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Language_reference_manual"/>, 
a <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Material_specification"/>, 
a <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Process_specification"/>, or 
a <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Test_specification"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition.source">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Organization"/> 
or the <express_ref linkend="Person_organization:arm:Person_organization_arm.Person_in_organization"/> responsible for 
the information of an  <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition.wr:WR1">
The <b>source</b> shall be provided and it's size shall be one.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Design_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Design_specification">
A <b>Design_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> that 
establishes the design specifications of products. A <b>Design_specification</b> may be an 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Interface_specification"/>. 
These specifications are not determined by other 
design or construction features or by referenced data.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Design_specification.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Fabrication_technology_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Fabrication_technology_specification">

A <b>Fabrication_technology_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Process_specification"/> 
that describes the technology used 
for parts and part families.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Fabrication_technology_specification.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Interface_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Interface_specification">

An <b>Interface_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Design_specification"/> 
that describes the characteristics and constraints necessary for correct 
interoperation between specified units.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Interface_specification.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Language_reference_manual +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Language_reference_manual">
A <b>Language_reference_manual</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> 
that defines the syntax and semantics of a computer interpretable language.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Language_reference_manual.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Material_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Material_specification">

A <b>Material_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> 
that specifies properties applicable to raw material, 
mixtures, or semi-fabricated material that are used in the fabrication of a product. A <b>Material_specification</b> may be 
a <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Surface_finish_specification"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Material_specification.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Process_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Process_specification"><p>
A <b>Process_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> that 
identifies and describes an activity to be performed on an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/> or 
<express_ref linkend="generic_material_aspects:arm:Generic_material_aspects_arm.Material_identification"/>. A 
<b>Process_specification</b> may be an 
<express_ref linkend="Assembly_technology:arm:Assembly_technology_arm.Assembly_technology_specification"/> or 
a <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Fabrication_technology_specification"/>.
</p><example>
<p>
<module_ref linkend="specification_document:4_entities:figure:ps">Figure 1</module_ref> illustrates
a detail from a <b>Process_specification</b> for an etching process.
</p>
</example>
<figure id="ps">
  <title>Process specification</title>
  <img src="ps.gif"/>
</figure>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Process_specification.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
