<!-- +++++++++++ Surface_finish_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Surface_finish_specification">
A <b>Surface_finish_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Material_specification"/> that is a collection of the 
properties applicable to surface textures or 
coatings either for a product in-process or a completed product.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Surface_finish_specification.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Test_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Test_specification">
A <b>Test_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> that 
provides information about the physical or functional testing of an 
<express_ref linkend="Product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Test_specification.additional_characterization">
the string value equal to 'design specification'.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Structured_text_id_in_document +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text_id_in_document">
<p>
 A <b>Structured_text_id_in_document</b> is a set of detailed information whose location in a <b>document</b> is directly referenced. The information is in the form of <b>text</b>, tables, and graphics in a human readable language, although the hard copy may be a report from computer interpretable files.  The same information may be included in multiple <b>document</b>s in different locations, and in that case different <b>Structured_text_id_in_document</b> would be populated for each <b>document</b>.  This Application Object supports the case where it is necessary to identify the different locations within the same <b>document</b> that a set of information exists.
</p></ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text_id_in_document.document">
specifies the <express_ref linkend="Document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/> that is the container for the information referenced by <b>Structured_text_id_in_document</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text_id_in_document.text">
specifies the unique <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Structured_text"/> that is the information for the <b>Structured_text_id_in_document</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text_id_in_document.identifier">
specifies the label that is the identification within the <b>document</b> of the  <express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Structured_text"/> referenced by <b>text</b> for the <b>Structured_text_id_in_document</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text_id_in_document.ur:UR1">
the <b>identifier</b> and <b>document</b> shall be unique within a population of the <b>Structured_text_id_in_document</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ get_document_definition ++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.get_document_definition">
The <b>get_document_definition</b> function returns the set of <express_ref linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition">Document_definitions</express_ref>
that are assigned to the specified <b>input</b> by the <express_ref linkend="document_assignment:arm:Document_assignment_arm.Document_assignment">Document_assignments</express_ref>,
having their <express_ref linkend="document_assignment:arm:Document_assignment_arm.Document_assignment.role"/> set to the specified <b>role</b>,
as <express_ref linkend="document_assignment:arm:Document_assignment_arm.Document_assignment.assigned_document">assigned_documents</express_ref>
and are of type specified by <b>type_name</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.get_document_definition.input">
the specified <express_ref linkend="document_assignment:arm:Document_assignment_arm.documented_element_select"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.get_document_definition.role">
the specified role of <express_ref linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition">Document_definitions</express_ref>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.get_document_definition.type_name">
the specified type of <express_ref linkend="document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition">Document_definitions</express_ref>.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>

